lavender and yellow inspired beach wedding color schemes 2015: We love saffron yellow partnered with lavender and dove white this season, but saffron still remains the forefront color for such a venue. It’s an obvious summery yellow shade that will always have a special place on a beach or at any summer or outdoor wedding. This color simply cannot be disliked due to its vibrant hue and happy go lucky vibes it gives us.
seafoam green and viola purple beach themed wedding color ideas: n this color palette, the addition of amethyst really gives a traditional oceanic palette a fresh look.

coral and aqua beach themed wedding color ideas for 2015: If you’ve been searching for that natural down–to-earth style, then these shades may just be right for you. Perfect for your typical bohemian wedding coral and gray shades give you that effortless charm.

2015 trending dusty blue and blush pink beach summer wedding color idea: This is such a beautiful color to use on a beach wedding, it’s not one we usually associate with sunshine and cocktails, but it really works, especially when done correct way with small accents of color, such as the groom’s tie or little ribbon details.

shades of green colors inspired beach wedding ideas 2015: These classic wedding colors don’t just give you the typical nautical theme, but what they do bring is vibrancy and radiance under the gleaming sun. These colors look fab on bridesmaids and if you have some fancy glass table-wear than they will glean outrageously on the table and create a gorgeous effect against the backdrop of the sun, sea and sand.
